        "role_in_text": "COO of Quantum Exponential",
        "occurrence_sentence": "Stuart Woods is the COO of Quantum Exponential, the UK's first enterprise venture capital fund focused on quantum technology.",
        "source_document": "https://thequantuminsider.com/2024/02/01/guest-post-quantum-exponentials-stuart-woods-in-conversation-with-mandy-birch"
      },
      {
        "entity": "Stuart Woods",
        "page": 13,
        "role_in_text": "COO of Quantum Exponential",
        "occurrence_sentence": "Stuart Woods is the COO of Quantum Exponential, the UK's first enterprise venture capital fund focused on quantum technology.",
        "source_document": "https://thequantuminsider.com/2024/02/01/guest-post-quantum-exponentials-stuart-woods-in-conversation-with-mandy-birch"
      },
      {
        "entity": "Stuart Woods",
        "page": 15,
        "role_in_text": "Interviewer",
        "occurrence_sentence": "This is especially crucial since well-managed consolidation is essential for successful outcomes as many companies are – and should be – specializing in different parts of the stack only. Many “quantum computing” companies specialize in component technologies that will comprise the supply chain of future high-performance quantum computers. Bringing all these specialized innovations together to create a fault-tolerant quantum computer is a systems engineering challenge not merely an assembly exercise. The sooner that we recognize that all quantum processor and related component companies should not be full-stack quantum computing companies – the better. Anyone remember JDSU? They were the component company that fueled the dot-com and telecom booms. Companies need to start working together to merge assets across the ecosystem and piece together these elemental sub-architectures. To discuss the short-term future of quantum computing, specifically regarding how the landscape may shift and consolidate, I had the pleasure of speaking with Mandy Birch.",
        "source_document": "https://thequantuminsider.com/2024/02/01/guest-post-quantum-exponentials-stuart-woods-in-conversation-with-mandy-birch"
      },
      {
        "entity": "Stuart Woods",
        "page": 16,
        "role_in_text": "Interviewer",
        "occurrence_sentence": "Stuart Woods: How do you see the topography of the industry shifting over the next few years?",
        "source_document": "https://thequantuminsider.com/2024/02/01/guest-post-quantum-exponentials-stuart-woods-in-conversation-with-mandy-birch"
      },
      {
        "entity": "Stuart Woods",
        "page": 17,
        "role_in_text": "Interviewer",
        "occurrence_sentence": "Stuart: From your perspective, having grown with the industry, what do you think is stopping these more productive and constructive forms of consolidation activity at the moment?",
        "source_document": "https://thequantuminsider.com/2024/02/01/guest-post-quantum-exponentials-stuart-woods-in-conversation-with-mandy-birch"
      },
      {
        "entity": "Stuart Woods",
        "page": 18,
        "role_in_text": "Interviewer",
        "occurrence_sentence": "Stuart: There are certain pockets of the industry that champion only one kind of qubit modality or another – you must find this very frustrating!",
        "source_document": "https://thequantuminsider.com/2024/02/01/guest-post-quantum-exponentials-stuart-woods-in-conversation-with-mandy-birch"
      },
      {
        "entity": "Stuart Woods",
        "page": 19,
        "role_in_text": "Guest speaker",
        "occurrence_sentence": "Stuart: A lot of the companies and technologies that are in play at the moment are being called quantum computing – by the companies themselves or by ministers and media who, in this relatively early phase of development, understand every quantum technology to be quantum computing.",
        "source_document": "https://thequantuminsider.com/2024/02/01/guest-post-quantum-exponentials-stuart-woods-in-conversation-with-mandy-birch"
      },
      {
        "entity": "Stuart Woods",
        "page": 20,
        "role_in_text": "interviewee",
        "occurrence_sentence": "Stuart: I completely agree. To facilitate this commercialization, we need the proper production infrastructure.",
